  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2040 mg
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: North America
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim
and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced, whites separated from greens). Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites, @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz}, and @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}. Cook, breaking up meat
into pieces, until sausage is browned and cooked through and scallions are softened,
~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in tomato and cook until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Once water is boiling, gently add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%oz} to #pot{}. Reduce to a low simmer.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente and floating to the top, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

> TIP: Gently shake strainer with ravioli in it to remove as much moisture as possible.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{1} and a squeeze of lemon juice into pan with sausage mixture.
Cook over low heat, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in
@sour cream{4%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until
> sauce reaches a creamy consistency.

Carefully stir ravioli into pan with sauce. Season with salt, pepper, and lemon juice to taste.

Divide ravioli mixture between bowls. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges on the side.